        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">07</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">I&rsquo;m buying into a private practice. How does that affect my personal mortgage?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">The practice buy-in note becomes a debt obligation in your personal DTI when personally guaranteed. If the note is paid from your share of partnership distributions, the monthly payment counts in DTI calculation. Sequencing matters: close your personal mortgage either BEFORE the buy-in (qualify on employed-period W-2 income) or AFTER a year of K-1 history establishes the new income level. For SBA-financed acquisitions, see our <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/professional-services/business-acquirer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">business acquirer mortgage guide</a> for coordination logistics.</div>
